                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89/982</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Economic Adviser</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Livesey</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-19">June 19,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State today told the Secretary of the Treasury that the latter
                    had full jurisdiction in war debt matters.</p>
                <p>This statement was made by the Secretary of State in the course of a conversation
                    which had not previously touched on war debt matters or on questions of the
                    respective jurisdictions of the Departments.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of the Treasury definitely noted the statement as disposing of a
                    question which had not previously been discussed. He took occasion to say that
                    the Department of State has given the Treasury Department better cooperation in
                    all matters of Treasury interest than any other Department has done.</p>
            </div>
